value.0: Yeh?
Mebbeh. Whut're yeh wantin' t' knauw?
Nup. Ah gaut m' auwn.
Dunnuh. An' yeh best dunnuh aither 'less yeh wanna seh th' dungeons, ayup.
Ayup. An' yeh tauk te much.
Nup. Heh daun' beh sehn much.
'Is beh th' raud t' th' est.
Daun' yeh dehr t' walk th' raud efter nichtfall. Ther beh speerits an' ghoosts an' uther fell crittoors abaut.

Mmm. Th' Uthgar' dun kilt a herd o' haurses laung tahm back, menneh yehr agau. Ther speerit caums back a' nicht, black as th' grehve an' breathin' fahr, 'tis said. Him what sees it aun th' raud daun' live t' tell th' staureh less'n heh run faster'n th' wind, ayup.
Ayup. Ol' Cutter Fahan dun cut hissel' daun lahk a treh an' daun' knauw better'n t' kep gauin'. Yeh watch fer 'im an' 'is axe, yeh watch!
'Is beh th' muntins.
Nup.
'Is beh Ostdur.
Nup.
Nothing, never mind.
Hello, goodwife. I was wondering if you could answer a few questions for me?
That's all, thanks. Have a nice day.
Is there any work to be had around here?
Then I'd best look elsewhere. Good <day/night> to you.
And I'm sure you do it very well. Can I ask you something else?
Who's this Magnus guy I keep hearing about?
I know nothing, and it seems I should keep it that way. Good bye, then.
Good advice. How about we change the subject?
The guards keep things on a pretty tight leash around here.
Then I'd better shut up. Bye, now.
Apparently. Do you have time to talk some more?
Do you think I could arrange to see the Axe himself?
I think I'll be disappearing myself, now.
Guess I'll strike that off my social calendar. Got time for another question?
What lies to the east of here?
The road, yes. To the east, got it. Is there anything else you can tell me about it?
Thanks for the information, goodwife.
Sounds like a good place to keep away from. Can you tell me anything else?
Spirits?
Thanks. Good bye now.
I've hardly understood a word you've said. Can I ask you something else?
You said something about ghosts?
Ghosts?
Thanks. Good bye now.
I think I might possibly have understood that. Can I ask you something else?
You mentioned spirits?
What lies to the west of here?
The mountains? Anything else?
You're a veritable encyclopedia.
Mm hm. Could you tell me something else?
Can you tell me a bit about this town?
I know that, old woman. Anything else you can tell me about it?
Right. Thanks for nothing.
I see. Could you perhaps answer some other questions?
